<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1481,1759]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
REMARKS.—This is the largest of the Ecuadorian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[707,830,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[707,830,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with body lengths of about 
<quantity box="[1243,1323,1481,1508]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="48.0">48 mm</quantity>
and wing spans of more than 
<quantity box="[365,460,1517,1544]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="120.0">120 mm</quantity>
. The basic brown and piceous coloration, the anterior extension of the postclypeus when viewed from the dorsal side and the fore wings have infuscation on the radial and radiomedial crossveins which easily distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName authority="Goding, 1925" authorityName="Goding" authorityYear="1925" box="[437,734,1589,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis box="[437,570,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">M. truncata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Goding, F. W." box="[577,734,1589,1616]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref70044" refString="Goding, F. W. (1925) Synopsis of the Cicadidae of Ecuador. Revista del Colegio Nacional Rocafuerte, 7, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1925">Goding, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1481,1759]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
DISTRIBUTION.—The species is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[683,754,1625,1651]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[765,878,1625,1651]" name="Colombia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[889,984,1625,1651]" name="Ecuador" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[994,1162,1625,1651]" name="French Guiana" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1172,1290,1625,1651]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1437,1626,1652]" name="Panama" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[159,325,1661,1687]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref71633" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; Sanborn 2011a; 2013; 2018c; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maes, J. - M. &amp; Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F." box="[666,853,1661,1688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref71321" refString="Maes, J. - M., Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. (2012) Cicadidae (Homoptera) de Nicaragua: catalogo ilustrado, incluyendo especies exoticas del Museo Entomologico de Leon. Revista Nicaraguense Entomologia, 72 (Suplemento 2), 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="2012">
Maes 
<emphasis box="[732,787,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M." box="[862,1113,1661,1688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="437 - 442" refId="ref74898" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M. (2012) Checklist of the cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Nicaragua including new records for seventeen species. Check List, 8, 437 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 8.3.437" type="journal article" year="2012">Sanborn &amp; Maes 2012</bibRefCitation>
) with recent records reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[191,242,1698,1724]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[257,434,1697,1724]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref74088" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2020 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Peru including the descriptions of twenty-four new species, three new synonymies, and thirty-seven new records. Zootaxa, 4785 (1), 1 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4785.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Sanborn 2020b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Goding, F. W." box="[453,619,1697,1724]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref70044" refString="Goding, F. W. (1925) Synopsis of the Cicadidae of Ecuador. Revista del Colegio Nacional Rocafuerte, 7, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1925">Goding (1925)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from Posorja, Guayas province and Macas, Morona Santiago province.
</paragraph>
